      "text": "CSS background-image"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The background-image property specifies an image to use as the background of an element."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "By default, the image is repeated so it covers the entire element."
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "body {  background-image: url(\"paper.gif\");}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "body {  background-image: url(\"bgdesert.jpg\");}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "other",
      "text": "Note: When using a background image, use an image that does not disturb the text."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The background image can also be set for specific elements, like the <p> element:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "p {  background-image: url(\"paper.gif\");}"
        }
      ]
    },
